!!!
%html
  %head
    %title Stories
    %link(rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css")
    %link(rel="stylesheet" href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/css/bootstrap.min.css")
    %link(rel="stylesheet" href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/css/bootstrap-theme.min.css")
    %script(src="//code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.0.min.js")
    %script(src="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/js/bootstrap.min.js")
  %body
    %div{:class => ""}
      = haml :"templates/nav"

    %div{:class => "container"}
      Welcome to the story wizard. We'll try to help you as much as we can with making a basic story.
      %p
        If you want to use more advanced features you can hit advanced after you are done with the story.
        Let's get starting. First we need some basic information about the story.
      %form{:action => "/mystories/edit/story", :method => "post", :role => "form", :class => "form-horizontal"}
        %fieldset
          %div{:class => "row form-group"}
            %div{:class => "col-md-2"}
              Every story needs a name
              %label{:for => "title"} Title:
            %input{:type => "text", :name => "", :value => "#{params['']}"}
            
          %div{:class => "row form-group"}
            %div{:class => "col-md-2"}
              so, what is this story about?
              %label{:for => "title"} Description:
            %input{:type => "text", :name => "", :value => "#{params['']}"}
  
          %div{:class => "row form-group"}
            %div{:class => "col-md-2"}
              we prefilled it with your profile name
              %label{:for => "author"} Author:
            %input{:type => "text", :name => "", :value => "#{params['']}"}
            
          %div{:class => "row form-group"}
            %div{:class => "col-md-2"}
              Where in the world?
              %label{:for => "title"} Area:
            %input{:type => "text", :name => "", :value => "#{params['']}"}
            
      %p
        Okay, let continue on with our first tag. Tags in TagStory is what a story is made up of.
        So a Story will usually have a lot of different tags that can all be connected. So watch out
        for repeating loops. You don't want your adventurers to walk in circles.
      %a{:href => "/mystories/wizard/tag", :class => "btn btn-default"}
        Add your first tag
